# Convert to mg/Sm3
# y_water * P_std / (R * T_std) * M_water * 1e6
print(f"Approximate water content: {y_water * 1e6:.0f} ppm(mol)")
```

=== 9.3.5 Effect of Gas Composition
<effect-of-gas-composition>
CPA correctly predicts the effect of gas composition on water content:

- #strong[CO$""_2$ increases water content]: CO$""_2$--water solvation makes the gas phase more hospitable for water molecules
- #strong[H$""_2$S increases water content]: similar solvation effect, even stronger than CO$""_2$
- #strong[Heavier hydrocarbons increase water content]: the gas becomes denser, accommodating more water
- #strong[Nitrogen decreases water content]: N$""_2$ is less hospitable to water than methane

These compositional effects are automatically captured by CPA through the association and solvation terms, without the need for empirical corrections.

=== 9.3.6 Water Dew Point Calculations
<water-dew-point-calculations>
